Module 2: Cybersecurity Fundamentals

Module 2 focuses on the core fundamentals of cybersecurity that every ethical hacker must understand. This module explains how data, systems, and networks are protected and why security is critical in todayâ€™s digital world. You will learn basic security principles used by organizations to defend against cyber attacks.

This module introduces key concepts such as Confidentiality, Integrity, and Availability (CIA Triad), common security controls, risk, threats, vulnerabilities, and attack surfaces. Understanding these fundamentals will help you better analyze systems during reconnaissance and exploitation phases in later modules.

What You Will Learn

What is Cybersecurity

CIA Triad (Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability)

Threats, vulnerabilities, and risks

Types of security controls (Administrative, Technical, Physical)

Attack surface and attack vectors

Basic security policies and best practices

Outcome

After completing this module, you will have a strong understanding of cybersecurity principles that support ethical hacking and defensive security.
